hi. when you add start end date time filter to a report , then the report don't look user preference for calendar type in user preferences selected. to resolve that do this in core: (hope if this is correct, developer add this code to core ) in the path: blocks/configurable_reports/components/filters/startendtime/plugin.class.php add following function in " plugin_startendtime " class: 
```text
public function jalali_to_gregorian($jy, $jm, $jd) {
    $jy += 1595;
    $days = -355668 + (365 * $jy) + (((int)($jy / 33)) * 8) + ((int)((($jy % 33) + 3) / 4)) + $jd + (($jm < 7)? ($jm - 1) * 31 : (($jm - 7) * 30) + 186);
    $gy = 400 * ((int)($days / 146097));
    $days %= 146097;
    if ($days > 36524) {
        $gy += 100 * ((int)(--$days / 36524));
        $days %= 36524;
        if ($days >= 365) $days++;
    }
    $gy += 4 * ((int)($days / 1461));
    $days %= 1461;
    if ($days > 365) {
        $gy += (int)(($days - 1) / 365);
        $days = ($days - 1) % 365;
    }
    $gd = $days + 1;
    $sal_a = array(0, 31, (($gy % 4 == 0 and $gy % 100 != 0) or ($gy % 400 == 0))?29:28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31);
    for ($gm = 0; $gm < 13 and $gd > $sal_a[$gm]; $gm++) $gd -= $sal_a[$gm];
    return array($gy, $gm, $gd);
}
```
