Ypiiie, I found the culprit! It's the file styles.css of the Configurable Reports plugin (mymoodle.mysite.com/blocks/configurable_reports/styles.css) The first three lines: 
```text
@import url("../blocks/configurable_reports/js/datatables/media/css/jquery.dataTables.css");


@import url("../blocks/configurable_reports/js/codemirror/lib/codemirror.css");


@import url("../blocks/configurable_reports/js/codemirror/addon/display/fullscreen.css");
```
 have to be changed to 
```text
@import url("/blocks/configurable_reports/js/datatables/media/css/jquery.dataTables.css");


@import url("/blocks/configurable_reports/js/codemirror/lib/codemirror.css");


@import url("/blocks/configurable_reports/js/codemirror/addon/display/fullscreen.css");
```
 (that is, remove the .. at the beginning of each url). After that, there are no more errors in the developer console and the three css files are listed and can be opened in the Sources tab of the developer tool (Chrome). Success!

Contact Juan on https://moodle.org/plugins/block_configurable_reports and ask him to remove the 'imports' but instead copy / paste each file's CSS into the blocks styles.css file -> https://github.com/jleyva/moodle-block_configurablereports/blob/MOODLE_30_STABLE/styles.css .  Or just do this yourself to remove the relative path.  Or edit your version and change the urls to be absolute paths, e.g. 
